1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:05,760
THIS DRAMA IS CREATED
FOR ENTERTAINMENT PURPOSES

2
00:00:05,840 --> 00:00:10,720
ALL CHARACTERS, SETTINGS
AND EVENTS ARE ENTIRELY FICTITIOUS

3
00:00:10,800 --> 00:00:15,920
THERE IS NO INTENT TO REFERENCE
ANY ORGANIZATIONS OR INDIVIDUALS

4
00:03:15,040 --> 00:03:17,600
The Seven Legends fell into my trap.

5
00:03:18,520 --> 00:03:21,280
Sergeant Dab was blown to pieces.

6
00:03:22,360 --> 00:03:24,440
The rest are being hunted.

7
00:03:30,320 --> 00:03:32,280
- Hey, I'm out of ammo.
- Hey.

8
00:03:33,120 --> 00:03:35,040
- I've got nothing left, bro.
- Damn.

9
00:03:44,160 --> 00:03:48,360
Or is this mission already
at a dead end for you guys?

10
00:04:06,800 --> 00:04:08,320
Take Mook away!

11
00:04:08,400 --> 00:04:09,880
- Go. Go.
- Dad, please.

12
00:04:09,960 --> 00:04:11,760
- Don't hurt Mr. Dan, please, Dad.
- Go.

13
00:04:11,840 --> 00:04:12,920
Hey.

14
00:04:19,959 --> 00:04:21,560
Same old habits, Sarge.

15
00:04:25,440 --> 00:04:27,200
Always disappearing without a word.

16
00:04:27,800 --> 00:04:29,440
Not even a thank you.

17
00:04:41,680 --> 00:04:42,520
Praew.

18
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:44,960
Are you hurt?

19
00:04:49,280 --> 00:04:51,320
Phoenix doesn't need me anymore.

20
00:04:51,400 --> 00:04:53,960
So he's silencing everyone
who's no longer useful.

21
00:04:58,080 --> 00:04:59,120
You were shot.

22
00:05:01,400 --> 00:05:03,320
You need to go to the hospital.

23
00:05:04,480 --> 00:05:08,120
Even you are being hunted.
If I show up there, I won't survive.

24
00:05:08,880 --> 00:05:09,800
But if we leave it like this…

25
00:05:09,880 --> 00:05:11,800
I don't die easily, Sarge.

26
00:05:11,880 --> 00:05:16,080
I worked for Phoenix.
I know how to survive.

27
00:05:17,440 --> 00:05:18,520
Praew.

28
00:05:19,920 --> 00:05:21,200
Go see a doctor.

29
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:23,680
I know a doctor who can help you.

30
00:05:25,080 --> 00:05:28,000
Help me, so we're even?

31
00:05:28,080 --> 00:05:29,800
So we don't owe each other
anything anymore?

32
00:05:29,880 --> 00:05:31,920
Stop being sarcastic.

33
00:05:33,160 --> 00:05:35,560
You came to help me. You betrayed them.

34
00:05:36,840 --> 00:05:39,040
Now I know that the kid I once saved…

35
00:05:40,480 --> 00:05:41,720
is back.

36
00:05:44,320 --> 00:05:47,240
Sarge, believe me.

37
00:05:47,960 --> 00:05:50,440
Right now, you can't beat Phoenix.

38
00:05:51,840 --> 00:05:52,960
Why?

39
00:05:53,040 --> 00:05:54,200
Right now,

40
00:05:54,760 --> 00:05:57,360
Phoenix is working with a mafia group

41
00:05:57,920 --> 00:05:59,280
that trades military-grade weapons.

42
00:06:00,280 --> 00:06:01,920
Their goal

43
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:06,680
is to use Pha Mok as a hub
to sell weapons to terrorists.

44
00:06:07,720 --> 00:06:09,040
Terrorists?

45
00:06:10,640 --> 00:06:12,840
They want to dominate the region.

46
00:06:13,440 --> 00:06:15,520
That's why
they reset their entire network.

47
00:06:16,600 --> 00:06:21,080
Once I knew too much,
they tried to get rid of me.

48
00:06:22,640 --> 00:06:23,920
Phoenix.

49
00:06:25,240 --> 00:06:27,560
It really isn't just cybercrime.

50
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:31,440
It's good you know now.
So we can clip their wings.

51
00:06:32,040 --> 00:06:33,120
Sarge.

52
00:06:34,080 --> 00:06:35,880
Don't throw your life away here.

53
00:06:37,440 --> 00:06:38,520
I can't, Praew.

54
00:06:39,760 --> 00:06:42,480
I won't let Phoenix destroy my country.

55
00:06:44,240 --> 00:06:46,720
Praew, you have to tell me

56
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:48,720
who Phoenix really is.

57
00:06:49,320 --> 00:06:50,640
We'll deal with them.

58
00:06:51,280 --> 00:06:54,040
And you'll be protected as a witness.

59
00:06:54,120 --> 00:06:55,680
You won't be held responsible.

60
00:07:11,800 --> 00:07:14,720
That's Phoenix's true identity?

61
00:07:17,800 --> 00:07:19,480
I never expected it.

62
00:07:21,120 --> 00:07:22,240
That bastard.

63
00:07:29,680 --> 00:07:30,560
Hey!

64
00:07:33,240 --> 00:07:34,280
Arab.

65
00:07:35,160 --> 00:07:36,400
Run!

66
00:07:38,960 --> 00:07:40,320
Hurry.

67
00:07:46,760 --> 00:07:47,840
Praew, hide here.

68
00:07:53,200 --> 00:07:54,400
Do you have a gun?

69
00:07:55,440 --> 00:07:56,560
No.

70
00:07:57,200 --> 00:07:58,640
We're screwed.

71
00:08:20,680 --> 00:08:23,080
Praew, Praew, Praew.

72
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:29,880
Sarge.

73
00:08:31,040 --> 00:08:32,240
Run.

74
00:08:34,159 --> 00:08:35,120
Run…

75
00:08:36,120 --> 00:08:37,120
Go.

76
00:09:11,520 --> 00:09:12,800
Hey.

77
00:09:17,480 --> 00:09:18,920
His name is Dan.

78
00:09:20,480 --> 00:09:22,240
He's one of the Seven Legends.

79
00:09:23,160 --> 00:09:24,800
We captured him for interrogation,

80
00:09:25,400 --> 00:09:28,000
but he won't tell us where the others are.

81
00:09:31,240 --> 00:09:33,360
So? Do you know him?

82
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:39,880
Okay.

83
00:09:40,520 --> 00:09:43,720
It's time for you to prove your loyalty

84
00:09:45,040 --> 00:09:47,000
and show that you're not a mole.

85
00:09:57,600 --> 00:09:58,600
Ratee.

86
00:10:01,080 --> 00:10:03,080
Please shoot him in the head for me.

87
00:10:04,560 --> 00:10:07,880
Prove your loyalty to me. Please.

88
00:10:12,120 --> 00:10:13,040
Now.

89
00:10:27,200 --> 00:10:30,120
You said you weren't a mole.

90
00:10:30,200 --> 00:10:32,920
This is your chance to prove it.

91
00:10:33,680 --> 00:10:35,680
Just blow his head off.

92
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:38,720
That's all it takes
to show me you're not a mole.

93
00:10:42,240 --> 00:10:43,120
Shoot him.

94
00:10:44,920 --> 00:10:45,800
Shoot him for me.

95
00:10:47,560 --> 00:10:48,760
Shoot!

96
00:10:58,760 --> 00:11:00,800
<i>The only thing I can hope for…</i>

97
00:11:01,960 --> 00:11:05,200
is you.

98
00:11:06,240 --> 00:11:08,960
That you'll help your dad

99
00:11:09,040 --> 00:11:10,360
become a good man again.

100
00:11:11,400 --> 00:11:13,640
Help him turn back to the right path.

101
00:11:14,920 --> 00:11:17,320
Please work with Dan.

102
00:11:18,120 --> 00:11:18,960
Please.

103
00:11:21,840 --> 00:11:22,920
Go.

104
00:11:24,320 --> 00:11:27,640
Dad. That's enough. Please. Mr. Dan.

105
00:11:27,720 --> 00:11:28,920
Dad, please don't hurt him.

106
00:11:29,880 --> 00:11:31,520
- Take Mook away!
- Dad.

107
00:11:32,520 --> 00:11:33,880
- Dad.
- Hey.

108
00:11:33,960 --> 00:11:36,200
- Don't. I said don't.
- Dad, I'm begging you.

109
00:11:36,280 --> 00:11:37,640
- Let Ms. Mook go.
- Let go.

110
00:11:58,960 --> 00:12:00,400
Shoot him!

111
00:12:03,640 --> 00:12:04,680
Boss.

112
00:12:05,320 --> 00:12:06,240
There's news from Arab.

113
00:12:06,320 --> 00:12:07,480
What?

114
00:12:07,560 --> 00:12:09,680
Sergeant Dab, leader
of the Seven Legends, is alive.

115
00:12:10,320 --> 00:12:11,480
Praewpan saved him.

116
00:12:11,560 --> 00:12:13,560
But Arab has dealt with her.

117
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:17,880
Sarge Dab isn't dead?

118
00:12:19,920 --> 00:12:21,440
That's how it should be.

119
00:12:21,520 --> 00:12:24,240
Our Sarge Dab is still alive.

120
00:12:25,320 --> 00:12:27,160
Your leader may still be alive.

121
00:12:27,240 --> 00:12:29,160
But you won't survive today.

122
00:12:31,400 --> 00:12:32,360
So what?

123
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:34,920
A guy like me is ready to die anytime.

124
00:12:35,480 --> 00:12:37,640
Die cool. Even win your daughter's heart.

125
00:12:38,720 --> 00:12:41,080
But you, you're her father,

126
00:12:41,800 --> 00:12:43,480
yet your wife and kid want nothing
to do with you. You know that?

127
00:12:46,960 --> 00:12:48,160
Get up.

128
00:12:49,360 --> 00:12:50,440
Wait.

129
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:52,560
You talk big.

130
00:12:53,440 --> 00:12:55,520
Is that all you've got?

131
00:12:55,600 --> 00:12:58,400
I don't feel a thing. But look at him.

132
00:12:58,480 --> 00:13:00,400
I bet your boss hurts real bad

133
00:13:01,280 --> 00:13:04,520
because he's disappointed
his own daughter and wife.

134
00:13:05,880 --> 00:13:08,480
In the end, you'll die alone
like an old stray dog

135
00:13:08,560 --> 00:13:10,200
with no one to care for you.

136
00:13:10,280 --> 00:13:11,320
Shoot him.

137
00:13:11,400 --> 00:13:12,440
Shoot him now. Shoot!

138
00:13:12,520 --> 00:13:14,080
Shoot! Shoot me!

139
00:13:14,160 --> 00:13:15,360
I said shoot!

140
00:13:16,720 --> 00:13:19,480
Shoot him now. Blow his brains out!

141
00:13:20,080 --> 00:13:24,480
Ouch, help! Help.

142
00:13:24,560 --> 00:13:25,680
Help.

143
00:13:25,760 --> 00:13:28,120
Help. Help.

144
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:30,400
What's wrong, miss?

145
00:13:30,480 --> 00:13:33,400
My stomach hurts. I need medicine.

146
00:13:34,040 --> 00:13:35,440
It hurts.

147
00:13:36,560 --> 00:13:37,760
Please calm down.

148
00:13:38,600 --> 00:13:39,960
I'll inform the boss.

149
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:46,040
Ouch, miss, no.

150
00:14:10,760 --> 00:14:13,000
Let go!

151
00:14:13,920 --> 00:14:14,840
Let go, miss.

152
00:14:14,920 --> 00:14:16,280
- Let go.
- Hey.

153
00:14:24,320 --> 00:14:25,880
You really think

154
00:14:25,960 --> 00:14:29,080
I'd load this gun with real bullets?

155
00:14:41,360 --> 00:14:42,400
Hey!

156
00:15:04,320 --> 00:15:06,600
Dan, go. Go now. Hurry.

157
00:15:10,480 --> 00:15:11,520
- Dad!
- Huh?

158
00:15:12,040 --> 00:15:13,120
Ms. Mook.

159
00:15:14,680 --> 00:15:15,640
Hold Mookda!

160
00:15:17,920 --> 00:15:18,920
‪What?

161
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:19,880
You can't help her anymore.

162
00:15:19,960 --> 00:15:23,440
You have to go back and help Sarge Dab
finish the Seven Legends' mission.

163
00:15:25,320 --> 00:15:27,360
If we run together,
none of us will make it. I'll cover you.

164
00:15:28,440 --> 00:15:29,480
Go.

165
00:15:39,720 --> 00:15:41,280
Fine. I surrender.

166
00:15:43,160 --> 00:15:44,120
Bring her to me!

167
00:16:02,000 --> 00:16:04,160
So now I finally know.

168
00:16:04,720 --> 00:16:06,920
You're the spy
who's been deceiving me all along.

169
00:16:16,880 --> 00:16:18,600
- Hey.
- Hey, hey.

170
00:16:18,680 --> 00:16:19,240
- Dan.
- Dan.

171
00:16:19,320 --> 00:16:20,400
- Hey.
- Dan.

172
00:16:24,240 --> 00:16:25,960
- Sit down.
- Slowly.

173
00:16:32,360 --> 00:16:34,840
Sarge, I'm sorry.

174
00:16:39,040 --> 00:16:41,440
You can't help her anymore.
You have to go back and help Sarge Dab

175
00:16:41,520 --> 00:16:43,480
finish the Seven Legends' mission.

176
00:16:45,400 --> 00:16:48,080
If we run together,
none of us will make it. I'll cover you.

177
00:16:48,160 --> 00:16:50,680
No. We go back for Sarge together.

178
00:16:51,560 --> 00:16:53,720
Just knowing he's alive is enough for me.

179
00:16:53,800 --> 00:16:56,760
So your duty now
is to bring my hope to him.

180
00:16:56,840 --> 00:16:57,920
Do you understand?

181
00:16:59,320 --> 00:17:00,960
What are you doing?

182
00:17:01,040 --> 00:17:02,920
Dan Mahittha, this is an order.

183
00:17:03,000 --> 00:17:05,040
If you disobey, the mission fails.

184
00:17:06,079 --> 00:17:08,359
Take my message to Sarge. Go.

185
00:17:09,359 --> 00:17:10,440
Go.

186
00:17:14,880 --> 00:17:17,480
Honestly, I wanted to disobey
Ms. Duangnet's order, but…

187
00:17:17,560 --> 00:17:19,960
It's fine. You did the right thing.

188
00:17:20,880 --> 00:17:22,040
She's the commander.

189
00:17:23,280 --> 00:17:26,800
But I don't agree
with the message she left for you.

190
00:17:26,880 --> 00:17:28,440
Me neither.

191
00:17:28,520 --> 00:17:30,640
You're going to lead us to wipe them out

192
00:17:30,720 --> 00:17:32,840
and not rescue her?

193
00:17:33,360 --> 00:17:37,200
Yes, Sarge. We're ready to split
to help her. Just give the order.

194
00:17:40,960 --> 00:17:42,640
All of you, that's enough.

195
00:17:43,720 --> 00:17:45,000
Stop acting reckless.

196
00:17:45,680 --> 00:17:47,600
Didn't you hear Director Pantong's order?

197
00:17:47,680 --> 00:17:49,520
Mission canceled in 24 hours.

198
00:17:49,600 --> 00:17:52,040
Go your separate ways. Go home.

199
00:17:52,120 --> 00:17:53,760
What are you waiting for?

200
00:17:53,840 --> 00:17:57,520
If anyone's still here, I'll beat you
one by one. Starting with you.

201
00:17:58,560 --> 00:18:02,520
Kla. You've found your love, haven't you?
Go back to your soulmate.

202
00:18:02,600 --> 00:18:04,600
Go home and take care of your family.
Don't you understand?

203
00:18:04,680 --> 00:18:05,720
Sarge.

204
00:18:06,800 --> 00:18:08,080
Stop acting cool.

205
00:18:08,160 --> 00:18:10,600
You're the one who cares

206
00:18:11,160 --> 00:18:12,640
about Ms. Duangnet the most.

207
00:18:14,320 --> 00:18:17,720
You all think the same as me, right?
He's telling us to leave

208
00:18:18,600 --> 00:18:19,720
because he's trying to go solo.

209
00:18:22,680 --> 00:18:23,600
Right?

210
00:18:24,440 --> 00:18:26,560
Solo my ass.

211
00:18:26,640 --> 00:18:29,720
I just got blown up. I'm not
going anywhere. I'm scared of dying!

212
00:18:29,800 --> 00:18:31,600
I'm going back to farming chickens.

213
00:18:31,680 --> 00:18:34,920
Scared of dying? Really?

214
00:18:35,760 --> 00:18:37,680
When you survived that bomb,

215
00:18:39,360 --> 00:18:40,840
you could've run.

216
00:18:40,920 --> 00:18:44,120
You could've slipped away alone.
But you didn't.

217
00:18:45,760 --> 00:18:48,040
Because you're the leader
of the Seven Legends.

218
00:18:49,000 --> 00:18:52,120
You'd never abandon us. Right?

219
00:18:54,400 --> 00:18:57,880
Sarge, I'm so damn proud

220
00:18:59,000 --> 00:19:00,200
to be one of the Seven Legends.

221
00:19:00,280 --> 00:19:02,560
Well, Phoenix is right there.

222
00:19:03,200 --> 00:19:04,480
Let's clip his wings.

223
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:07,080
Ms. Duangnet's sacrifice won't be in vain.

224
00:19:07,880 --> 00:19:08,960
Yes, Sarge.

225
00:19:10,840 --> 00:19:12,600
We fight shoulder to shoulder.

226
00:19:13,320 --> 00:19:14,400
If we die, we die together.

227
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:18,200
Sarge, I know.

228
00:19:18,280 --> 00:19:20,000
I can see through you.

229
00:19:20,080 --> 00:19:23,560
You don't want them dying with you.

230
00:19:23,640 --> 00:19:25,320
But tell me honestly,

231
00:19:25,400 --> 00:19:26,960
if you go alone,

232
00:19:27,040 --> 00:19:30,080
can you save her? Huh?

233
00:19:31,040 --> 00:19:33,880
- Yeah.
- You can't.

234
00:19:33,960 --> 00:19:37,480
Exactly. You all see it, right?

235
00:19:38,640 --> 00:19:42,480
So we bring the name "Seven Legends"
back to glory,

236
00:19:43,560 --> 00:19:45,040
just like the generation before us.

237
00:19:46,440 --> 00:19:47,560
Seven Legends.

238
00:19:49,080 --> 00:19:50,120
Seven Legends.

239
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:56,080
Sarge,

240
00:19:56,720 --> 00:19:58,920
when are you going to tell us?

241
00:19:59,520 --> 00:20:02,360
From the information you got,
who is Phoenix?

242
00:20:08,120 --> 00:20:11,720
I told you before.
If I ever find out you're the spy,

243
00:20:12,680 --> 00:20:14,000
you'll pay.

244
00:20:14,880 --> 00:20:16,320
Do whatever you want.

245
00:20:16,960 --> 00:20:20,320
You'll never find the Seven Legends.

246
00:20:20,400 --> 00:20:23,320
We'll see how long
you can keep acting tough.

247
00:20:23,400 --> 00:20:26,600
Dying in the line of duty
is something I've always been ready for.

248
00:20:28,120 --> 00:20:29,240
Enough.

249
00:20:34,680 --> 00:20:36,800
Boss, give me a little more time.

250
00:20:37,480 --> 00:20:39,960
She's about to tell us
where the Seven Legends are.

251
00:20:40,720 --> 00:20:42,840
If you knew who this woman is,

252
00:20:44,040 --> 00:20:47,040
what she's been trained for,
what she's endured,

253
00:20:48,080 --> 00:20:51,920
you'd know torture won't make her talk.

254
00:20:53,040 --> 00:20:54,320
Her name is Duangnet,

255
00:20:55,680 --> 00:20:59,680
leader of the previous spy unit.
The only survivor.

256
00:21:00,920 --> 00:21:04,200
But what's interesting is her father.

257
00:21:09,400 --> 00:21:10,240
So,

258
00:21:12,360 --> 00:21:14,480
I can't let her die yet.

259
00:21:15,760 --> 00:21:18,800
She's still useful to me.

260
00:21:20,080 --> 00:21:22,320
So you're Phoenix.

261
00:21:29,240 --> 00:21:30,480
Congratulations.

262
00:21:31,800 --> 00:21:33,120
You finally know the truth.

263
00:21:34,520 --> 00:21:36,000
But knowing it now

264
00:21:37,240 --> 00:21:39,080
is too late.

265
00:21:43,480 --> 00:21:45,920
<i>Sriwong Prakaipruek, Angel of Merit.</i>

266
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:51,120
A former general who left the battlefield
for the business world.

267
00:21:51,200 --> 00:21:55,440
Built a billion-dollar real estate empire
for a sustainable society.

268
00:21:57,480 --> 00:22:00,160
But this time,
it's bigger than cybercrime.

269
00:22:00,800 --> 00:22:02,320
He's aiming for something bigger.

270
00:22:02,400 --> 00:22:05,520
He wants to lead
a transnational terrorist organization.

271
00:22:15,760 --> 00:22:17,600
- Here.
- One moment, please.

272
00:22:20,880 --> 00:22:22,280
Why are you following me?

273
00:22:22,360 --> 00:22:23,800
I knew it.

274
00:22:23,880 --> 00:22:25,560
You came here alone

275
00:22:25,640 --> 00:22:27,520
to finish the mission yourself,
didn't you?

276
00:22:30,040 --> 00:22:33,880
A tiger without claws like you,
if I wasn't around,

277
00:22:33,960 --> 00:22:35,280
would just be a burden.

278
00:22:35,360 --> 00:22:36,200
Tueng.

279
00:22:36,280 --> 00:22:40,000
I'm not just some useless desk officer.

280
00:22:40,080 --> 00:22:44,560
If you see me stretch a little,
you'll be shouting

281
00:22:44,640 --> 00:22:45,920
wow, wow, wow, yeah.

282
00:22:46,760 --> 00:22:48,520
Whoa! What is that?

283
00:22:56,480 --> 00:22:59,400
I didn't expect to see you here, Pantong.

284
00:23:00,400 --> 00:23:01,600
Sriwong?

285
00:23:02,760 --> 00:23:07,000
How long has it been?

286
00:23:07,080 --> 00:23:08,040
Since I…

287
00:23:08,120 --> 00:23:11,360
Since you left your post as general
to chase business full-time.

288
00:23:14,080 --> 00:23:15,600
It's been a long time.

289
00:23:16,120 --> 00:23:18,440
I do miss the old days.

290
00:23:18,520 --> 00:23:21,520
I've wanted to get together,
but as you know,

291
00:23:21,600 --> 00:23:24,360
I have business and the foundation work.

292
00:23:24,960 --> 00:23:26,560
I have to thank you.

293
00:23:26,640 --> 00:23:28,240
Thanks to your foundation,

294
00:23:28,320 --> 00:23:30,720
our children got scholarships.

295
00:23:30,800 --> 00:23:32,080
Hey.

296
00:23:32,160 --> 00:23:35,040
One must never forget hardship.

297
00:23:35,120 --> 00:23:38,200
When you have enough,
you share with those who don't.

298
00:23:40,000 --> 00:23:42,560
That's why I got invited here.

299
00:23:43,800 --> 00:23:46,880
If I invest in this new city project,

300
00:23:47,480 --> 00:23:52,360
people here could have the same quality
of life as those in the big cities.

301
00:23:52,440 --> 00:23:53,920
Did you get invited here?

302
00:23:54,000 --> 00:23:55,000
Yes.

303
00:23:55,720 --> 00:23:59,320
I was invited to preside over the opening
of the Pha Mok City project.

304
00:24:00,000 --> 00:24:03,080
Come on. We haven't seen each other
in ages and you're still talking business?

305
00:24:03,160 --> 00:24:05,720
Let's grab some coffee

306
00:24:05,800 --> 00:24:06,960
and talk about old times.

307
00:24:07,040 --> 00:24:08,880
Hey, wait. I can't today.

308
00:24:08,960 --> 00:24:12,080
Maybe next time.
I have something to take care of.

309
00:24:18,160 --> 00:24:21,280
By "something", do you mean this?

310
00:24:33,960 --> 00:24:37,240
So they want you to trade the lives
of the Seven Legends for Ms. Duangnet?

311
00:24:37,320 --> 00:24:39,200
They are real pains in the ass.

312
00:24:39,280 --> 00:24:41,440
Now that they have the upper hand,
they're acting tough.

313
00:24:43,640 --> 00:24:45,240
It must be a trap, sir.

314
00:24:45,760 --> 00:24:47,280
Someone like Phoenix

315
00:24:47,360 --> 00:24:49,360
would never keep his word.

316
00:24:49,440 --> 00:24:50,480
I know.

317
00:24:51,480 --> 00:24:53,800
No matter how worried I am about Duangnet,

318
00:24:55,440 --> 00:24:58,840
I won't trade the Seven Legends' lives.

319
00:24:59,360 --> 00:25:02,920
They're trying to create chaos
within the Seven Legends

320
00:25:03,000 --> 00:25:04,400
to distract us.

321
00:25:05,120 --> 00:25:07,280
Based on the intel from Sarge Dab,

322
00:25:07,880 --> 00:25:10,120
I got similar deep intel too.

323
00:25:10,640 --> 00:25:12,280
Right now,

324
00:25:12,360 --> 00:25:15,680
there's unusual military movement
along the border.

325
00:25:15,760 --> 00:25:18,520
And a buildup of heavy war weapons,

326
00:25:18,600 --> 00:25:20,520
with no clear objective.

327
00:25:22,080 --> 00:25:23,840
They're definitely connected.

328
00:25:24,440 --> 00:25:28,480
All those weapons
the anti-government forces are preparing

329
00:25:28,560 --> 00:25:30,960
must be the major deal that allows Phoenix

330
00:25:31,040 --> 00:25:33,320
to negotiate with terrorist mafias.

331
00:25:33,400 --> 00:25:34,880
Yeah.

332
00:25:34,960 --> 00:25:37,040
If this transaction succeeds,

333
00:25:37,840 --> 00:25:38,840
Phoenix

334
00:25:38,920 --> 00:25:43,280
will be known as an arms dealer
supporting terrorists,

335
00:25:43,360 --> 00:25:45,680
not just as a cybercriminal anymore.

336
00:25:47,360 --> 00:25:51,440
That's why they want us focused only
on our own lives and Ms. Duangnet's life,

337
00:25:51,520 --> 00:25:53,880
so we don't interfere
with their bigger objective.

338
00:26:02,200 --> 00:26:04,000
This battle is heavier than ever.

339
00:26:05,920 --> 00:26:07,840
That's why I ordered a withdrawal.

340
00:26:09,480 --> 00:26:10,680
But I didn't expect…

341
00:26:13,000 --> 00:26:14,480
that you'd all keep fighting.

342
00:26:17,200 --> 00:26:18,440
What's with you?

343
00:26:18,520 --> 00:26:21,560
Because the name Seven Legends
wasn't a free gift in a snack box.

344
00:26:22,120 --> 00:26:24,760
It's earned with heart and skill, sir!

345
00:26:24,840 --> 00:26:28,000
That's cool.

346
00:26:28,080 --> 00:26:30,920
So, tell them, sir.

347
00:26:31,000 --> 00:26:32,880
Let them know we're not afraid to die.

348
00:26:32,960 --> 00:26:34,120
Yeah.

349
00:26:35,280 --> 00:26:36,320
I think you're gonna die.

350
00:26:36,400 --> 00:26:39,120
Tell them you're ready to trade
the lives of the Seven Legends

351
00:26:39,200 --> 00:26:40,640
for Ms. Duangnet!

352
00:26:40,720 --> 00:26:41,920
For Ms. Duangnet!

353
00:26:42,000 --> 00:26:43,760
For Ms. Duangnet!

354
00:27:05,120 --> 00:27:06,400
Excuse me, miss.

355
00:27:07,320 --> 00:27:08,280
Let me check the food first.

356
00:27:08,960 --> 00:27:10,960
Is that necessary? It's just food.

357
00:27:19,600 --> 00:27:20,680
Please eat something.

358
00:27:35,360 --> 00:27:36,880
You saw his face, didn't you?

359
00:27:38,200 --> 00:27:41,120
The real identity of Phoenix
you've been searching for.

360
00:27:53,600 --> 00:27:54,880
I heard

361
00:27:55,440 --> 00:27:58,800
that tomorrow,
they'll make an offer to your father

362
00:28:00,120 --> 00:28:02,480
to trade the Seven Legends' lives for you.

363
00:28:07,320 --> 00:28:08,560
Time's up, miss.

364
00:28:24,840 --> 00:28:25,840
Please.

365
00:28:33,640 --> 00:28:36,080
During the press conference
for the Pha Mok Complex earlier,

366
00:28:36,160 --> 00:28:38,200
the media response was overwhelming, Boss.

367
00:28:38,280 --> 00:28:41,800
I assure you,
every <i>baht</i> you invest will be worth it.

368
00:28:45,800 --> 00:28:47,920
You really are good
at putting on a show, huh?

369
00:28:48,600 --> 00:28:51,120
Is that why you arranged
the different exchange locations?

370
00:28:51,200 --> 00:28:53,720
You have so many spies.

371
00:28:54,440 --> 00:28:56,680
I'll shoot them in the head
and bury them on the spot.

372
00:28:59,680 --> 00:29:01,480
- How long do we have to go?
- Hey.

373
00:29:01,560 --> 00:29:03,480
Get down! Go.

374
00:29:04,280 --> 00:29:05,520
It's hard to walk.

375
00:29:05,600 --> 00:29:06,800
- Go.
- Yeah.

376
00:29:06,880 --> 00:29:08,840
- Go.
- Yeah, I know.

377
00:29:09,680 --> 00:29:11,520
- Sit down.
- Hey, what?

378
00:29:11,600 --> 00:29:14,640
- Sit down.
- Hey, ow.

379
00:29:14,720 --> 00:29:16,760
- Can't you do it nicely?
- Yeah, go easy.

380
00:29:17,360 --> 00:29:19,120
Hey, take off their face covers.

381
00:29:24,080 --> 00:29:25,920
- My eyes hurt.
- You can just tell me nicely.

382
00:29:29,440 --> 00:29:30,720
<i>Confirm, Boss.</i>

383
00:29:31,400 --> 00:29:34,480
<i>The Seven Legends</i>
<i>came to exchange as agreed.</i>

384
00:29:50,000 --> 00:29:50,840
Sergeant Dab.

385
00:29:51,960 --> 00:29:53,200
Today, you're done.

386
00:29:58,320 --> 00:30:01,000
What? You tried to catch a koi fish
but got a catfish instead.

387
00:30:02,240 --> 00:30:04,400
Deal's off, Boss. Sarge Dab isn't here.

388
00:30:04,480 --> 00:30:06,080
Huh? Dab what? Take this.

389
00:30:06,160 --> 00:30:08,240
Hey! What's the meaning of this?

390
00:30:27,040 --> 00:30:27,880
Hold her.

391
00:30:36,640 --> 00:30:37,960
Ta-da.

392
00:30:38,040 --> 00:30:39,000
Hey.

393
00:30:39,760 --> 00:30:42,280
All your lives and ours
are in my hands now,

394
00:30:42,360 --> 00:30:43,800
in exchange for the Seven Legends' lives.

395
00:30:43,880 --> 00:30:45,080
Hey, don't move.

396
00:30:46,480 --> 00:30:50,000
This bomb
has a blast radius of 300 meters.

397
00:30:50,080 --> 00:30:52,920
Even national athletes can't outrun that.
Don't think you can.

398
00:31:04,960 --> 00:31:06,720
You guys are good.

399
00:31:06,800 --> 00:31:08,120
- Wow, so comfortable.
- Whoa.

400
00:31:08,200 --> 00:31:09,280
You sat there chilling, bastard?

401
00:31:09,360 --> 00:31:11,040
Take this.

402
00:31:11,640 --> 00:31:12,480
‪Alright.

403
00:31:18,880 --> 00:31:20,040
Just die here together.

404
00:31:24,600 --> 00:31:25,440
What's that?

405
00:31:26,360 --> 00:31:29,400
A grenade. Run!

406
00:31:36,000 --> 00:31:37,520
Pantong. Sergeant Dab.

407
00:31:38,400 --> 00:31:39,480
So this is your move?

408
00:31:39,560 --> 00:31:41,600
That's right. Impressive, isn't it?

409
00:31:41,680 --> 00:31:45,120
Now stop thinking we're rookie spies.
You idiot.

410
00:31:48,280 --> 00:31:49,520
Tueng, report.

411
00:31:49,600 --> 00:31:50,800
Thanks, Tueng.

412
00:31:52,400 --> 00:31:55,880
Your team got taken down
by my Seven Legends.

413
00:31:56,480 --> 00:31:58,880
Right now, Arab already fled.

414
00:31:58,960 --> 00:32:02,240
The game's turned. Send Duangnet over now.

415
00:32:02,320 --> 00:32:04,760
Hey, be careful.

416
00:32:04,840 --> 00:32:07,160
One blast
and there won't even be bodies left.

417
00:32:09,480 --> 00:32:12,800
I dare to stand here.
I dare to use this method

418
00:32:12,880 --> 00:32:14,400
because I've already
made peace with death.

419
00:32:14,480 --> 00:32:16,880
If I can't catch you today,
we die together.

420
00:32:16,960 --> 00:32:20,280
The rest of the Seven Legends
can carry on the mission anyway.

421
00:32:21,800 --> 00:32:24,560
You and Sergeant Dab are impressive.

422
00:32:25,840 --> 00:32:27,320
But I still have a surprise.

423
00:32:27,400 --> 00:32:28,240
Hey.

424
00:32:31,080 --> 00:32:32,320
- Hey, Mook.
- Dad.

425
00:32:32,840 --> 00:32:33,600
- Boss.
- Dad.

426
00:32:33,680 --> 00:32:34,480
- That's my daughter.
- Stop!

427
00:32:34,560 --> 00:32:35,920
- Mook.
- I said stop.

428
00:32:38,400 --> 00:32:41,680
Tomorrow,
they'll make an offer to your father

429
00:32:43,040 --> 00:32:45,400
to trade the Seven Legends' lives for you.

430
00:32:47,120 --> 00:32:48,520
Time's up, miss.

431
00:33:00,520 --> 00:33:01,440
Please.

432
00:33:36,280 --> 00:33:37,800
Hey! The bomb! Run!

433
00:33:37,880 --> 00:33:38,800
Go hide.

434
00:33:46,240 --> 00:33:47,480
Who helped them, sir?

435
00:33:48,320 --> 00:33:49,640
You okay, Ms. Duangnet?

436
00:33:49,720 --> 00:33:51,480
I'm fine. Just a scratch.

437
00:33:52,040 --> 00:33:52,920
Sarge, are you hurt?

438
00:33:53,000 --> 00:33:54,600
I'm not hurt.

439
00:33:54,680 --> 00:33:57,000
What were you thinking
pulling a stunt like this?

440
00:33:57,080 --> 00:33:59,920
What if there had been a spark?
We'd all be dead!

441
00:34:01,080 --> 00:34:03,120
Here. Whoa, I just touched it.

442
00:34:03,720 --> 00:34:04,800
Please hold this for me.

443
00:34:06,480 --> 00:34:09,480
I'm not stupid, sir. They're all fake.

444
00:34:10,199 --> 00:34:12,760
Who would bring real bombs?
I love my life too.

445
00:34:12,840 --> 00:34:14,080
I'm no hero.

446
00:34:15,040 --> 00:34:15,920
Take it back.

447
00:34:16,520 --> 00:34:17,560
It's going to explode.

448
00:34:19,600 --> 00:34:20,440
How are you?

449
00:34:20,520 --> 00:34:21,639
I'm fine, Dad.

450
00:34:29,639 --> 00:34:30,639
Are you really okay?

451
00:34:31,159 --> 00:34:33,880
It's far from my heart. Thanks, Sarge.

452
00:34:34,400 --> 00:34:36,840
Your plan was insane. Dying together?

453
00:34:38,000 --> 00:34:39,880
Well, if I wasn't destined
to be with you in this life,

454
00:34:39,960 --> 00:34:42,280
maybe I will be in the next one.

455
00:34:43,520 --> 00:34:45,840
Sarge, I've got the intel.

456
00:34:48,360 --> 00:34:49,480
Why aren't you saying it?

457
00:34:49,560 --> 00:34:50,800
I found the information. You say it.

458
00:34:50,880 --> 00:34:53,000
Idiot.
You walked in all cool and dramatic.

459
00:34:54,639 --> 00:34:56,120
According to criminal records,

460
00:34:56,920 --> 00:34:57,880
his name is Igor.

461
00:34:57,960 --> 00:35:00,560
He's the right-hand man of Sergey Malinov.

462
00:35:00,640 --> 00:35:03,040
Sergey's a mafia arms dealer

463
00:35:03,120 --> 00:35:05,360
and the mastermind
behind international terrorism.

464
00:35:06,800 --> 00:35:09,840
These guys don't show themselves
unless they're cornered.

465
00:35:10,440 --> 00:35:13,560
So that means Phoenix's deal
with Sergey didn't go smoothly.

466
00:35:13,640 --> 00:35:15,040
That's why he sent his right-hand man.

467
00:35:15,640 --> 00:35:18,320
Correct. Based on satellite images,

468
00:35:18,400 --> 00:35:21,680
Phoenix's group is heading
toward the border right now.

469
00:35:21,760 --> 00:35:24,240
It's likely the area
Director Pantong's intel identifies

470
00:35:24,320 --> 00:35:27,960
as a weapons stockpile
belonging to anti-government forces.

471
00:35:29,600 --> 00:35:34,440
So we have to stop this major
arms deal from going through.

472
00:35:37,120 --> 00:35:38,520
This is big, Sarge.

473
00:35:40,560 --> 00:35:42,440
Phoenix, Sergey,

474
00:35:43,040 --> 00:35:46,640
and the anti-government forces
across the border supplying weapons.

475
00:35:47,400 --> 00:35:50,080
They've got an army. We've got this.

476
00:35:52,160 --> 00:35:53,160
This handful.

477
00:35:55,520 --> 00:35:58,920
By the time we contact the army
for backup,

478
00:35:59,000 --> 00:35:59,920
it'll be too late.

479
00:36:01,240 --> 00:36:03,800
If it's too late, so what?
What are we afraid of?

480
00:36:04,600 --> 00:36:06,600
We're all rookie spies,

481
00:36:06,680 --> 00:36:09,160
yet we nearly clipped their wings.

482
00:36:09,240 --> 00:36:11,680
No matter where they run,
even across the border,

483
00:36:11,760 --> 00:36:13,120
we follow and finish it.

484
00:36:13,200 --> 00:36:14,680
- Yeah!
- Yeah!

485
00:36:15,400 --> 00:36:16,240
With this handful.

486
00:36:16,320 --> 00:36:17,960
- Whoa.
- This handful?

487
00:36:18,640 --> 00:36:19,560
Sarge is right.

488
00:36:20,240 --> 00:36:22,320
If we retreat now, it's surrender.

489
00:36:22,400 --> 00:36:24,360
Everything we've done becomes nothing.

490
00:36:36,800 --> 00:36:38,640
Boss. I'm sorry, Boss.

491
00:36:39,160 --> 00:36:40,080
Boss.

492
00:36:40,640 --> 00:36:43,480
They're both useless to me now.

493
00:36:43,560 --> 00:36:45,840
- Boss, no. Mook.
- Drag them away and finish them.

494
00:36:45,920 --> 00:36:47,280
- Dad. Dad.
- Mook. Mook.

495
00:36:47,360 --> 00:36:48,880
- Dad, please. Mook. Mook.
- Dad! Dad!

496
00:36:48,960 --> 00:36:51,240
- Go.
- Boss, please.

497
00:36:51,320 --> 00:36:53,000
Dad! Dad!

498
00:37:29,680 --> 00:37:33,480
You have four hours to deal with Phoenix.

499
00:37:34,080 --> 00:37:35,280
This mission is classified.

500
00:37:35,920 --> 00:37:37,480
It has nothing to do with the government.

501
00:37:39,000 --> 00:37:40,720
<i>Whether you succeed or not,</i>

502
00:37:42,440 --> 00:37:44,400
<i>your names won't be recorded.</i>

503
00:37:45,640 --> 00:37:46,800
<i>If you die,</i>

504
00:37:49,040 --> 00:37:51,000
<i>your bodies won't be brought back.</i>

505
00:38:06,560 --> 00:38:07,920
The Seven Legends.

506
00:38:08,000 --> 00:38:09,480
Go kill them all.

507
00:38:09,560 --> 00:38:10,800
- No, no.
- Dad.

508
00:38:10,880 --> 00:38:11,840
- No!
- Come here.

509
00:38:16,760 --> 00:38:19,080
Hold them off. I'll handle Arab myself.

510
00:38:39,200 --> 00:38:41,000
- Arab.
- Sergeant Dab.

511
00:39:06,560 --> 00:39:08,200
They are real pains in the ass.

512
00:39:09,320 --> 00:39:12,400
Now that they have the upper hand,
they're acting tough.

513
00:39:12,480 --> 00:39:13,600
Yeah, pull.

514
00:39:13,680 --> 00:39:15,360
It's too late now.

515
00:39:15,440 --> 00:39:18,120
What? You just stopped like a robot.

516
00:39:18,200 --> 00:39:19,360
Sarge Dab, sit down.

517
00:39:19,440 --> 00:39:20,720
Lift him up and sit him down.

518
00:39:20,800 --> 00:39:21,880
Lift him up like this.

519
00:39:21,960 --> 00:39:23,120
Okay. Next.

520
00:39:23,200 --> 00:39:25,200
- Phoenix.
- Now I wanna change something.

521
00:39:25,280 --> 00:39:26,400
Lift him like that.

522
00:39:27,480 --> 00:39:31,880
Border Patrol.
Advanced camouflage training

523
00:39:31,960 --> 00:39:35,080
with special air units.

524
00:39:36,200 --> 00:39:37,800
She has a negotiation certificate…

525
00:39:37,880 --> 00:39:40,040
Does it taste good?

526
00:39:53,520 --> 00:39:54,760
- Hey!
- Hey.

527
00:39:55,400 --> 00:39:56,520
What?

528
00:39:57,080 --> 00:39:59,400
Stay still.
Move and I'll blow your guts out.

529
00:39:59,480 --> 00:40:00,640
Stay still.

530
00:40:07,640 --> 00:40:08,680
Okay. Take them out.

531
00:40:08,760 --> 00:40:09,960
Kla, enough!

532
00:40:10,040 --> 00:40:12,760
- Go. Go.
- Cut.

533
00:40:14,400 --> 00:40:16,080
- Cut.
- Cut.

534
00:40:16,160 --> 00:40:18,920
- His body is full of holes already.
- Stay still.

535
00:40:19,000 --> 00:40:20,280
Stay still.

536
